      • possibleOverlappingObjects

        protected com.google.common.base.Predicate<ObjectMask> possibleOverlappingObjects(ObjectMask source,
                                                                                  Iterable<WithConfidence<ObjectMask>> others)
        Description copied from class: ReduceElementsGreedy
        Finds a subset of others that possibly overlap with the source element.

        This is not a definite list of element, but must contain all possible overlapping element, and should be efficient.

        This is the first filtering step. The resulting list will then be further filtered by ReduceElementsGreedy.includePossiblyOverlappingObject(T, T).

        Specified by:
        possibleOverlappingObjects in class ReduceElementsGreedy<ObjectMask>
        Parameters:
        source - the element we are currently processing, for which we search for possibly overlapping element
        others - other element that could possibly overlap with source but need to be filtered.
